{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"946324e4-6031-4494-90b2-3fd01b5fa95c","content":"This template is **not ready** to publish. It's missing the required `$schema` property and a few recommended fields:\n\n| Issue | Severity |\n|-------|----------|\n| Missing `$schema` | Recommended — enables IDE validation |\n| Missing `groupIdentity` | Important for NuGet — groups template versions |\n| Missing `precedence` | Needed when multiple versions coexist |\n| Missing `description` | Required by NuGet gallery for discoverability |\n| Missing `defaultName` | Minor — controls default project name |\n\nAt minimum, add `description` (NuGet won't display well without it) and `groupIdentity` (enables version updates). A publish-ready version would look like:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\",\n  \"identity\": \"MyCompany.WebApi.CSharp\",\n  \"groupIdentity\": \"MyCompany.WebApi\",\n  \"precedence\": 100,\n  \"name\": \"My Web API Template\",\n  \"description\": \"A template for creating Web API projects.\",\n  \"shortName\": \"mywebapi\",\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nWould you like me to update the file with these additions?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"56adad7d-c3b7-43ae-8bdb-f40fc04f19ca","outputTokens":285,"requestId":"1C16:14859A:AADCC71:B99ABB8:69FD34E8"},"id":"57b27862-32c7-4714-b7be-2bafb11eedee","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:57:20.022Z","parentId":"e32faa6d-4b89-44db-864c-90005d416978"}
